<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                    <head>No. 495.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-02-27"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 27, 1879</date>.
                            (Received March 24.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 98.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At about 4 p.m. on the 25th instant General
                        Guzman Blanco arrived in Caracas. The town was duly decorated and embannered
                        for the occasion, and the <hi rend="italic">entrée</hi> was accompanied by a
                        movement of the people, discharges of cannon, and explosion of rockets.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JEHU BAKER.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>